> put away journal

You close the journal.
> knock five times

> knock five times

The lock clicks and the front door creaks open. The long nose of Professor P emerges from the doorway.

"Five knocks...you must be Dr. Carter's assistant! Come in, come in!" he says.

Go WEST to enter the log house.
> w

> w

The log house is dark, but quite cozy. Professor P leads you towards a faded leather chair then sits opposite you. He limps as he walks; likely an old injury.

Every wall is covered with bookshelves. There's a small desk in one corner.

The front door is to the EAST.

> ask professor about gate

> ask professor about gate

"So you want to travel beyond the wall. What are you prepared to risk on such a quest? The elusive Serpent's Eye may lurk at the summit, but in between lies many untold dangers, to which I can personally attest."

He points a bony finger at your chest.

"Are you fully prepared to suffer the same fate as your predecessors? YES or NO?"
> y

> y

"You will need to show proof of your bravery in order to travel beyond the wall." He walks over to his desk and unlocks one of the drawers. Inside is an AMULET.

"This amulet was given to me by the island Chieftain when I first ventured into the jungle many years ago. It's the twin to the one he carried."

He ties the amulet around your neck. "It will protect you. Never, ever take it off."
> tell professor about q-n8

> tell professor about q-n8

Professor P looks puzzled for a moment. "Q-N8?....Q-N8!"

He leaps up and hobbles over to a dusty chess set on his desk. You watch as he studies the board very carefully. Then he moves the white queen.

"He beat me! All these years I thought I had him on the ropes, and that bespectacled bumpkin pulls out the perfect move! Go on, take a LOOK at the board."
> look at chess board

> look at chess board

You look at the dusty old chess board. A game looks to be in progress, but you fail to grasp anything beyond that.

"Do me a favour and take this GOLD COIN to him. He won it fair and square."
