For several hours you claw your way through the thick jungle growth, dodging low hanging branches, enormous roots, and more species of creepy-crawly than you ever knew existed. Just as you are nearing exhaustion, you emerge from a thick mass of leaves and discover a fork in the trail on the edge of a deep ravine.

You can see a SIGN pointing to the WEST and EAST. Head SOUTH to return to the village.
