From the personal journal of Dr. J. H. Carter.

Press any key to continue.
Our leader appears incapable of providing even the minimum level of authority over his warriors and this expedition. His insistence on preventing any attempt to obtain the stone key has led to great frustration on my part.

Press any key to continue.
He even refuses to offer any translation for the strange markings we have encountered thus far. He has instead chosen to put his trust in an ancient and intricate vine rope system that he believes will allow him to reach the temple while avoiding any potential dangers.

Press any key to continue.
Unbeknownst to the group, I have begun work on a crude translation myself and, though largely a matter of trial and error, I am confident that my work will prove fruitful - and far more sensible.

Press any key to continue.
You put the page in your pocket.
> rest

> rest

Warm, dry, and safe (for the moment), you decide to catch up on some much-needed rest. You close your eyes and are soon in a deep sleep.

Press any key to continue.
Hours pass.

More hours pass.

You begin to have the strangest dream...that spiders are crawling all over your neck...you brush them away but they return seconds later...

Press any key to continue.
Your eyes fly open and you sit up with a start. The firepit is full of glowing embers and everything beyond the mouth of the cave is still dark.

You catch a glimpse of a second flickering light source vanishing through an extremely narrow tunnel behind one of the boulders on the NORTH wall of the cave.

You also realize you are feeling a lot lighter.
