You throw the rock at the nearest wall. From the sharp crack you assume you've made contact - a suspicion confirmed seconds later by a cachophony of percussion that shakes the very ground beneath your feet.

The noise eventually fades, although the skull-pounding headache you've acquired is likely to last a bit longer.
