After several days and nights of study, my translation efforts have experienced a significant breakthrough. I have just discovered that the island of Ankrum has, in fact, two distinct written languages.

Press any key to continue.
Much as Latin emerged from a collection of earlier languages, the script used on the unusual device appears to be a much more recent evolution of the symbols which adorn many of the island's other landmarks. With this knowledge I have been able to apply my earlier research towards finding a translation that aligns with our own relatively primative English.

Press any key to continue.
I must be cautious, however. The Chieftain seems to be growing suspicious of my nightly work, almost as if he knows more than he has revealed. Should he try to obstruct my efforts in any way, I may be forced to complete the last stretch of this journey alone.

Press any key to continue.
