Any thoughts of exhaustion quickly fade away as your eyes fall upon the ancient glory of the temple of the Serpent's Eye and its glistening white marble walls.

Two tall statues, carved in the likeness of monstrous snakes, stand guard on either side of the entrance. You are shocked to discover no gates, spikes, or drawbridge to block your progress. The little voice inside your head openly questions the convenience of such a gift.

The temple lies to the NORTH, or you can descend the mountain to the SOUTH.
