> n

> n

As you step cautiously past the threshold of the iron gate, your flashlight inexplicably flickers and dies.
The brightness of the treasure room assaults your eyes. You are able to make out a white marble altar beside the wall opposite the iron gate. A massive pit with no visible bottom dominates most of the room’s centre.

You observe that the light is not coming from the sun, but rather from the large gemstone sitting atop the altar. It takes you a few moments to grasp the magnitude of this discovery. You are staring at the SERPENT’S EYE.

You are so entranced with the glowing gem that you almost fail to notice the iron gate slamming shut behind you.
> take eye

> take eye

Any fears you may have had previously quickly melt away as you are lulled towards the seductive glow of the Serpent’s Eye. You don’t pause to consider whether the faint singing you hear is real or just your imagination.

Your fingertips are mere inches away when you hear a cold, distinct CLICK.

Press any key to continue.

In the otherworldly light it takes you a moment to make out the identity of the bedraggled figure standing before you.

“I knew I could always count on the tenacity of my finest student,” she says. “Although your thirst for solving puzzles always did outweigh your aptitude for detecting deceit.”

Dr. Josephine H. Carter waves a pistol - your pistol - in your general direction.

Press any key to continue.

You notice the amulet hanging around her neck. “The Chieftain gladly leapt to his death rather than allow me to complete my quest. The remaining warriors may have needed some... encouragement.”

She raises her pistol as if to punctuate this statement. “It’s a shame he had to take his own amulet into the abyss with him.”

Press any key to continue.

“Did you not notice it strange that my journal, not to mention each subsequent page I placed along your path, was conveniently found when and where it was? I knew my dire warning to stay away from the island would have the opposite effect, and every new bit of insight you stumbled across would lead you further up the mountain.”

She points towards your flashlight. “Did you not think it odd that, of all things, a pair of fresh batteries would just happen to be sitting in my camp? I wanted you to be here with me, so I’d have exactly what I needed to complete my life’s work.”

Press any key to continue.

Carter chuckles to herself. “I decided the best way to draw you here was to set up a scavenger hunt of sorts. I’m so fortunate to have a student who does exactly what they’re told at every turn.”

Carter places her free hand on the Serpent’s Eye. Her head arches back as if absorbing some mystical energy from its touch. When she speaks, it’s no longer Carter’s voice you hear, but rather a shallow rasping sound, as if her words were carried on the wind itself.

She lifts the large gem from its cradle with one hand. “Now, at long last, everything has fallen into place...including the final piece of the puzzle…”

Press any key to continue.

Her eyes burst open, and you can see the light of the Serpent’s Eye within them. She trains her gaze on you.

“...a sacrifice.”

Blinding light pours from the Serpent’s Eye, accompanied by a low fog that drifts across the floor before cascading over the edge of the pit.

Press any key to continue.

A low pulsing sound drifts up from the depths of the void, and the fog rises once more, twisting and shaping its form until it assumes the shape of a colossal grey COBRA with glowing eyes that match Dr. Carter’s.

It wheels about and bears its fangs. You estimate you have two seconds at the most to act.
> play flute

> play flute

Fully aware that you may only have a few breaths left, you choose to apply one of them to the silver flute.

The grey cobra seems to ripple at the soothing tones before pausing its attack.

You may have just bought yourself three more seconds of existence. Use them wisely.
> throw peel at carter

> throw peel at carter

Recalling your favourite Keystone Cops picture, you hurl the banana peel at Dr. Carter. In the rolling fog she fails to notice it land at her feet.

The resulting slip is one for the history books. It seems to happen over the course of many minutes; her legs fly up until they’re almost horizontal with the ground, and her arms extend in a purely reflexive motion in a vain attempt to catch herself. The pistol falls from her grasp, bounces once on the marble floor, and tumbles into the pit.

Press any key to continue.

She scrambles back to her feet, still clutching the Serpent’s Eye and rubbing her elbow. “And to think I was going to recommend you for tenure.”

Then she notices the amulet lying on the ground.

“No-” is all she can bring herself to say as she lunges towards the amulet. But the cobra, seeing her completely unprotected, swirls around her like a grey whirlwind, drowning out her cries.

A moment later it is all over.

Press any key to continue.

The serpent seems to vanish in the same way it appeared, dissipating into wisps of fog before returning to the Serpent’s Eye, which is now lying where Dr. Carter stood mere seconds earlier. There is no trace of her.

Press any key to continue.

You quickly retrieve the amulet from the floor.
> take eye

> take eye

You crouch down and retrieve the Serpent's Eye from the floor. It seems to wink at you as you stare into its swirling heart.

Do you try to STEAL the Serpent's Eye, or do you RETURN it to the altar?
> put eye on altar

> put eye on altar

It doesn’t take you long to decide that the corrupting power of the Serpent’s Eye has no place in the hands of the human race, and you return the legendary stone to the altar.

You are extremely relieved when the iron gate creaks open seconds later.

You retrieve Professor P's amulet. Perhaps you should return it to him.

Press any key to continue.
You pause to take one last look at the magnificent temple, knowing full well you will most likely never return.

However, when all is still, you're convinced you can still hear the Serpent's Eye calling to you...begging you to return...

Go SOUTH to descend the mountain.
